IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: THE ROGUE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION (RCCF) WAS ESTABLISHED TO SUPPORT AND PROMOTE THE EDUCATIONAL, SCIENTIFIC, AND CHARITABLE ACTIVITIES OF ROGUE COMMUNITY COLLEGE (RCC). THE FOUNDATION ACCOMPLISHES ITS PURPOSE BY FOSTERING COMMUNITY INTEREST IN THE BROADENING OF EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES, SOLICITING AND DEVELOPING GRANTS AND GIFTS, INVESTING AND MANAGING FUNDS AND ACQUIRING AND DISPOSING OF REAL AND PERSONAL PROPERTY ON BEHALF OF RCC. THESE FUNDS ARE USED TO PROVIDE EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES FOR STUDENT SUCCESS, SUPPORT FOR COLLEGE PROGRAMS, FACULTY ADVANCEMENT, INSTRUCTIONAL ENHANCEMENT, CAMPUS ENRICHMENT. THE FOUNDATION ALSO SERVES AS A CITIZEN ADVISORY GROUP TO THE BOARD OF EDUCATION OF THE RCC DISTRICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part V, Line 4: Intended uses of the endowment fund.
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE INCOME FROM THE PERMANENTLY RESTRICTED ENDOWMENTS IS RESTRICTED FOR SCHOLARSHIPS AND OTHER PROGRAM SUPPORT.

ROGUE COMMUNITY COLLEGE FOUNDATION IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501 (C) (3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. IN ADDITION THE ORGANIZATION QUALIFIES FOR THE CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTION DEDUCTION UNDERSECTION 170(B)(1)(A)(VI) AND HAS BEEN CLASSIFIED AS AN ORGANIZATION THAT IS NOT A PRIVATE FOUNDATION UNDER SECTION 509 (A) (1) OF THE CODE. INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 513(A) DEFINES AN UNRELATED TRADE OR BUSINESS OF AN EXEMPT ORGANIZATION AS ANY TRADE OR BUSINESS WHICH IS NOT SUBSTANTIALLY RELATED TO THE EXERCISE OR PERFORMANCE OF ITS EXEMPT PURPOSE. NO INCOME OF THE ORGANIZATION IS CONSIDERED UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME, AND ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR REVENUE TAXES HAS BEEN ACCRUED. AS OF JUNE 30TH, THE ORGANIZATION HAS DETERMINED THAT IT HAS NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS REQUIRING ACCRUAL AND DISCLOSURE UNDER FASB ASC 740-10-50. THE FEDERAL INCOME TAX RETURNS OF THE ORGANIZATION ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE IRS FOR GENERALLY THREE YEARS.

THE ORGANIZATION'S PROCEDURES FOR MONITORING THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS ARE AS FOLLOWS; EACH RECIPIENT OF A CASH GRANT FROM THE FOUNDATION IS REQUIRED TO FILE A REPORT AT THE END OF THE GRANT PERIOD. THE REPORT MUST DETAIL THE USE OF THE FUNDS INCLUDING REPORTING BUDGET AND OUTCOMES COMPARED WITH PROJECTIONS SHOWN IN THE ORIGINAL GRANT APPLICATION. RECIPIENTS OF NON-CASH ASSISTANCE MUST CONFIRM RECIPT OF THE IN-KIND ITEMS AND VERIFY USE AS REPORTED IN THE ORIGINAL APPLICATION. THE REPORTS ARE REVIEWED BY THE PROJECT GRANT COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FINANCE COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE FORM 990 AND RECOMMENDS IT FOR ACCEPTANCE TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE FORM 990 IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD FOR REVIEW AND ACCEPTANCE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS REVIEWED ANNUALLY AND BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST ON AN ANNUAL BASIS. BOARD MEMBERS ARE OCCASIONALLY REMINDED OF THEIR RESPONSIBILITY TO DECLARE CONFLICT WHEN IT EXISTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS SALARY IS DETERMINED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE AND THE COLLEGE PRESIDENT, USING COMPARABLE DATA FOR OTHER SIMILAR NON-PROFIT AND COMMUNITY COLLEGE POSITIONS THROUGHOUT THE REGION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICTS OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
